<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Clerics are soloable at lower lvls, though once they get to 10 or 15 they really cant do it so well because creatures hp goes up faster than our mana/dmg spells. Our buffs are unbeatable, our heals are naturally stronger than any class, untill you get AA's. But Honimek is right, you MUST like helping other people, and you have to not mind being a backup. Clerics these days (for the most part) have one role, and one role only. They sit, until they need to heal and then they stand and cast, just to sit again. We spend alot of time sitting on our butts, but not unbearably so. As a cleric you are expected to be good at what you do, and have reasonably good equip, plus a decent mana pool. Lots of times, if someone dies, its the clerics fault (even if it isn't) so be ok with being blmaed for things you didn't cause. Be accustomed to being bothered with /tell's for buffs or rezzes, or heals or cures, because it happens. Downfalls in the main are that cleric, on an inate level (when you make them, it just happens) we get an experence DECREASE. we get i believe its 3% less exp per a kill than a normal player. We get something of the like when we level for HP and AC, but our buffs easily counter that. Another pit is that we really ony get spells in three schools, rather then all 5; we usaly get only Aleration, Abduration, and Evocation. The other two schools, Divination and Conjuration are somewhat rare. Advantages are simple, we get a 3% inate healing bonus. Means if a druid of the same level, casts the same heal, while he may do (lets say) 1k hp, you will do 1030. Not much, but when you take into account our high ones that do more, it helps. NOTE: CH is exempt from any help, no matter what, only AA's can effect it (not even sure if they can). We easily get the best buffs for hp/ac, thats hands down. We get Rez, and although we are no longer the only class that gets them, we get 96% rez at 56 which is rather early in levels, plus we get our AA rez, that does 100% with no health loss, debuff, or mana loss at all, simply brings you back in a perfect state (awsome aint it?). We have bnetter undead dmg spells than any class, even necro's or at least as far as i've looked we do. Over all, its a VERY VERY VERY VERY painful class to level until you get to your 50's, then its normal from there on. But in the end, its very worth it.</p>
